(TaskRunner pid=3881298) I need to find the difference between the maximum and minimum possible values of x, where x% of students gave different answers at the beginning and end of the school year.\n\nLet me set up the problem systematically.\n\nLet's say there are 100 students total (for simplicity, since we're dealing with percentages).\n\nAt the beginning:\n- 50 students answered "Yes"\n- 50 students answered "No"\n\nAt the end:\n- 70 students answered "Yes" \n- 30 students answered "No"\n\nLet me define variables for the different groups:\n- Let $a$ = students who changed from "No" to "Yes"\n- Let $b$ = students who changed from "Yes" to "No"\n- Let $c$ = students who kept "Yes" (didn't change)\n- Let $d$ = students who kept "No" (didn't change)\n\nFrom the given information:\n- Initially: 50 answered "Yes", 50 answered "No"\n- Finally: 70 answered "Yes", 30 answered "No"\n\nThis gives us:\n- Students who kept "Yes": $c = 50 - b$ (since 50 started with "Yes" and $b$ changed to "No")\n- Students who kept "No": $d = 50 - a$ (since 50 started with "No" and $a$ changed to "Yes")\n- Students who answered "Yes" at the end: $a + c = 70$\n- Students who answered "No" at the end: $b + d = 30$\n\nSubstituting:\n- $a + (50 - b) = 70 \Rightarrow a - b = 20$\n- $b + (50 - a) = 30 \Rightarrow b - a = -20$\n\nThese equations are consistent and give us $a - b = 20$.\n\nThe total number of students who changed their answers is $x = a + b$.\n\nFrom $a - b = 20$, we get $a = b + 20$.\n\nSo $x = a + b = (b + 20) + b = 2b + 20$.\n\nNow I need to find the constraints on $b$.\n\nSince we can't have more students changing than there were at the beginning:\n- $a = b + 20 \leq 50$ (since at most 50 students started with "No")\n- $b \leq 50$ (since at most 50 students started with "Yes")\n\nFrom $a = b + 20 \leq 50$, we get $b \leq 30$.\n\nAlso, since $a = b + 20 \geq 0$ and $b \geq 0$, we have $b \geq 0$.\n\nTherefore: $0 \leq b \leq 30$\n\nWhen $b = 0$: $a = 20$, so $x = 20 + 0 = 20$\nWhen $b = 30$: $a = 50$, so $x = 50 + 30 = 80$\n\nLet me verify these extreme cases:\n\nCase 1: $b = 0, a = 20$\n- Students who kept "Yes": $c = 50 - 0 = 50$\n- Students who kept "No": $d = 50 - 20 = 30$\n- Final "Yes" answers: $a + c = 20 + 50 = 70$ ✓\n- Final "No" answers: $b + d = 0 + 30 = 30$ ✓\n\nCase 2: $b = 30, a = 50$\n- Students who kept "Yes": $c = 50 - 30 = 20$\n- Students who kept "No": $d = 50 - 50 = 0$\n- Final "Yes" answers: $a + c = 50 + 20 = 70$ ✓\n- Final "No" answers: $b + d = 30 + 0 = 30$ ✓\n\nBoth cases work, so the range of x is from 20 to 80.\n\nThe difference between maximum and minimum values of x is: $80 - 20 = 60$\n\n<tool_call>\n{"name": "python", "arguments": {"code": "print('Maximum x value:', 80)\nprint('Minimum x value:', 20)\nprint('Difference:', 80 - 20)"}}\n</tool_call><|im_end|>\n<|im_start|>user\n<tool_response>\nMaximum x value: 80\nMinimum x value: 20\nDifference: 60\n\n</tool_response><|im_end|>\n<|im_start|>assistant\nThe difference between the maximum and minimum possible values of x is $\boxed{60}$.<|im_end|>
